dcterms:creator: Yann LeCun
dcterms:description: The MNIST dataset consists of 55,000 samples for training and 11,000 samples for testing, each representing a handwritten digit from 0 to 9, formatted as 28x28 pixel images. It is commonly used for benchmarking classification tasks in machine learning.
dcterms:title: MNIST dataset

dcterms:description: The Air Quality dataset contains hourly measurements of various air quality indicators and temperature, collected from sensor devices over a period from March 10, 2004, to April 4, 2005. It is used for regression tasks to predict air quality metrics.
dcterms:title: Air Quality dataset
